  <a href="#1" id="1">
   REGIONAL COURTS AND STRIKES
  </a>
  <a href="#2" id="2">
   Thousands of miners in the northern Vorkuta region are expanding their strike and some are blocking coal shipments, the Soviet news media reported on Nov. 2, 1989.
  </a>
  <a href="#3" id="3">
   The news media gave these accounts of the latest strikes: Workers at the Vorgashor mine in the Arctic Circle, the largest mine in the Vorkuta region, continued their strike for an eighth day, according to Tass.
  </a>
  <a href="#4" id="4">
   A regional court in Vorkuta ruled that the latest round of strikes is illegal but did not impose any penalties.
  </a>
  <a href="#5" id="5">
   Soviet officials have said the strikes could force fuel rationing during the Soviet Union's severe winter.
  </a>
